os</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":20,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas Giggs was born in 1362, in Norfolk, England, United Kingdom. He married Margaret of Rollesby about 1389, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in May 1420, in Rollesby, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 58."},"et":{"1362–May 1420":"1362–mai 1420","1374–Female":"1374–Surnud","1385–1440":"1385–1440","1362–1420":"1362–1420","1420":"1420","May 1420":"mai 1420","1385":"1385","about 1389":"umbes 1389","1440":"1440","1374":"1374","1362":"1362","1372":"1372","1382":"1382","Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Rollesby, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Rollesby, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"1362–May 1420":"1362–toukokuu 1420","1374–Female":"1374–Kuollut","1385–1440":"1385–1440","1362–1420":"1362–1420","1420":"1420","May 1420":"toukokuu 1420","1385":"1385","about 1389":"noin 1389","1440":"1440","1374":"1374","1362":"1362","1372":"1372","1382":"1382","Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Rollesby, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Rollesby, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England","England":"Eng